# Add Allocation Tracking Instrumentation

**Purpose**: Establish baseline metrics before migration to validate improvements.

## What to Implement

Add compile-time optional allocation tracking to the frame acquisition hot path:

```rust
// crates/daq-driver-pvcam/src/components/acquisition.rs

#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicU64, Ordering};

#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
pub static FRAME_ALLOCS: AtomicU64 = AtomicU64::new(0);
#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
pub static ALLOC_BYTES: AtomicU64 = AtomicU64::new(0);

// In the frame loop, around line 2789 (the to_vec call):
#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
{
    FRAME_ALLOCS.fetch_add(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
    ALLOC_BYTES.fetch_add(copy_bytes as u64, Ordering::Relaxed);
}

// Also track Arc allocation around line 3000:
#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
{
    FRAME_ALLOCS.fetch_add(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
    ALLOC_BYTES.fetch_add(std::mem::size_of::<Frame>() as u64, Ordering::Relaxed);
}
```

## Add Feature Flag

```toml
# crates/daq-driver-pvcam/Cargo.toml
[features]
alloc_tracking = []
```

## Add Reporting Function

```rust
/// Get allocation statistics since last reset
#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
pub fn get_alloc_stats() -> (u64, u64) {
    (
        FRAME_ALLOCS.load(Ordering::Relaxed),
        ALLOC_BYTES.load(Ordering::Relaxed),
    )
}

/// Reset allocation counters
#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
pub fn reset_alloc_stats() {
    FRAME_ALLOCS.store(0, Ordering::Relaxed);
    ALLOC_BYTES.store(0, Ordering::Relaxed);
}
```

## Add Test to Capture Baseline

```rust
#[cfg(feature = "alloc_tracking")]
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_baseline_allocations() {
    // Setup mock or real camera
    let driver = create_test_driver().await;

    reset_alloc_stats();

    driver.start_stream().await.unwrap();
    tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(10)).await;
    driver.stop_stream().await.unwrap();

    let (allocs, bytes) = get_alloc_stats();
    let frames = driver.frames_captured().await.unwrap();

    println!("Frames: {}", frames);
    println!("Allocations: {} ({:.2}/frame)", allocs, allocs as f64 / frames as f64);
    println!("Bytes: {} ({:.2} MB/frame)", bytes, bytes as f64 / frames as f64 / 1_000_000.0);

    // Document baseline - expect ~2 allocs/frame, ~16 MB/frame
}
```

