## Initial lib.rs Skeleton

```rust
//! Generic object pool for zero-allocation resource management.
//!
//! This module provides a reusable pool pattern for any type that needs
//! pre-allocation and recycling. The pool uses a semaphore for synchronization,
//! eliminating per-access locking overhead.
//!
//! # Example
//!
//! \`\`\`ignore
//! let pool = Pool::new_with_reset(5, || vec![0u8; 1024], |buf| buf.fill(0));
//! let mut item = pool.acquire().await;
//! item[0] = 42;
//! drop(item);  // Automatically returned to pool and reset
//! \`\`\`

// Implementation will be ported from planmeca in next task

pub struct Pool<T> {
    _marker: std::marker::PhantomData<T>,
}

pub struct Loaned<T> {
    _marker: std::marker::PhantomData<T>,
}
```

