# Port Loaned<T> Implementation from planmeca

**Purpose**: Copy the RAII guard implementation that provides automatic pool return.

## Source Location

```
/Users/briansquires/code/planmeca/crates/pool/src/lib.rs
Lines 292-424
```

## Key Components to Port

### 1. Loaned<T> Struct (lines 310-313)

```rust
pub struct Loaned<T: Send + 'static> {
    pool: Arc<Pool<T>>,
    idx: usize,
}
```

### 2. Core Access Methods (lines 315-352)

```rust
impl<T: Send + 'static> Loaned<T> {
    /// Get immutable reference (takes RwLock read)
    pub fn get(&self) -> &T { ... }

    /// Get mutable reference (takes RwLock read)
    pub fn get_mut(&mut self) -> &mut T { ... }

    /// Get reference to owning pool
    pub fn pool(&self) -> &Arc<Pool<T>> { ... }
}
```

### 3. Clone Support (lines 354-383)

```rust
impl<T: Clone + Send + 'static> Loaned<T> {
    /// Clone contents and return, consuming loan
    pub fn clone_item(self) -> T { ... }

    /// Try to clone into new pool slot (non-blocking)
    pub fn try_clone(&self) -> Option<Self> { ... }
}
```

### 4. Trait Implementations (lines 386-424)

```rust
impl<T: Send + 'static> Deref for Loaned<T> { ... }
impl<T: Send + 'static> DerefMut for Loaned<T> { ... }
impl<T: Clone + Send + 'static> Clone for Loaned<T> { ... }
impl<T: Send + 'static> Drop for Loaned<T> { ... }
```

## Critical: Drop Implementation

The Drop implementation is what makes pool reclamation automatic:

```rust
impl<T: Send + 'static> Drop for Loaned<T> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        self.pool.release(self.idx);
    }
}
```

This ensures pool slots return when Loaned goes out of scope.

## Potential Enhancement: Unsafe get_unchecked()

The current implementation takes RwLock on every access. For hot paths, consider:

```rust
/// Get reference without lock (safe because semaphore guards)
/// 
/// # Safety
/// The semaphore permit ensures exclusive access to this slot.
/// This method skips the RwLock for performance-critical code.
#[inline]
pub unsafe fn get_unchecked(&self) -> &T {
    // Skip RwLock - we know we have exclusive access via semaphore
    // Note: Only safe if pool never shrinks (it doesn't)
    &*(*self.pool.slots.data_ptr())[self.idx].get()
}
```

**Decision**: Port as-is first, optimize later if profiling shows contention.

