# Sub-Epic 3: FrameData Type & Pool Integration

**Phase**: 2
**Parent Epic**: PVCAM Memory Pool Architecture Migration
**Depends On**: Sub-Epic 1 (Pool Crate), Sub-Epic 2 (Arrow Removal)

## Overview

This sub-epic creates the FrameData type and integrates the pool into the PVCAM acquisition loop, replacing the per-frame to_vec() allocation with pool slot reuse.

## Key Insight: The Unavoidable Copy

The PVCAM SDK controls when circular buffer slots are reused (after unlock_oldest_frame). We MUST copy frame data before unlock. BUT:

- **Current**: Copy into freshly allocated Vec<u8> (8 MB allocation per frame)
- **Proposed**: Copy into pre-allocated pool slot (0 allocation after warmup)

## FrameData Type Design

```rust
// New file: crates/daq-driver-pvcam/src/components/frame_pool.rs

use daq_pool::{Pool, Loaned};

/// Raw frame data with metadata, suitable for pooling.
/// Buffer is pre-allocated and reused across frames.
pub struct FrameData {
    /// Pre-allocated pixel buffer (capacity >= max frame size)
    pub data: Vec<u8>,
    /// Actual bytes written (may be < capacity)
    pub actual_len: usize,
    /// Frame dimensions
    pub width: u32,
    pub height: u32,
    pub bit_depth: u32,
    /// Frame identification
    pub frame_number: u64,
    pub timestamp_ns: u64,
    /// Optional metadata
    pub exposure_ms: Option<f64>,
    pub roi_x: u32,
    pub roi_y: u32,
}

impl FrameData {
    /// Create new FrameData with pre-allocated buffer
    pub fn new(capacity: usize) -> Self {
        Self {
            data: vec![0u8; capacity],
            actual_len: 0,
            width: 0,
            height: 0,
            bit_depth: 16,
            frame_number: 0,
            timestamp_ns: 0,
            exposure_ms: None,
            roi_x: 0,
            roi_y: 0,
        }
    }

    /// Reset metadata for pool reuse (buffer stays allocated)
    pub fn reset(&mut self) {
        self.actual_len = 0;
        self.frame_number = 0;
        self.timestamp_ns = 0;
        self.exposure_ms = None;
        // Keep data buffer allocated - this is the whole point!
    }

    /// Get actual pixel data slice
    pub fn pixels(&self) -> &[u8] {
        &self.data[..self.actual_len]
    }
}

pub type LoanedFrame = Loaned<FrameData>;
pub type FramePool = Pool<FrameData>;

/// Create frame pool matching PVCAM circular buffer configuration
pub fn create_frame_pool(pool_size: usize, frame_capacity: usize) -> Arc<FramePool> {
    Pool::new_with_reset(
        pool_size,
        move || FrameData::new(frame_capacity),
        FrameData::reset,
    )
}
```

## Integration into AcquisitionState

Add to AcquisitionState struct:
