# Add Pool Factory and Type Aliases

**Purpose**: Create convenient type aliases and factory function for frame pools.

## Add to frame_pool.rs

```rust
// Type aliases for frame-specific pool usage
pub type LoanedFrame = Loaned<FrameData>;
pub type FramePool = Pool<FrameData>;

/// Create a frame pool with appropriate configuration.
/// 
/// # Arguments
/// * \`pool_size\` - Number of frame slots to pre-allocate
/// * \`frame_capacity\` - Buffer size per frame in bytes
/// 
/// # Recommended Sizing
/// 
/// | Circular Buffer | Pool Size | Rationale |
/// |-----------------|-----------|-----------|
/// | 20 frames | 40+ | 2x for consumer headroom |
/// | 32 frames | 64+ | 2x for consumer headroom |
/// 
/// # Example
/// 
/// \`\`\`ignore
/// // For 2048x2048 @ 16-bit = 8 MB frames, 32 circular buffer
/// let pool = create_frame_pool(64, 8_388_608);
/// 
/// // Acquire a frame slot
/// let mut frame = pool.acquire().await;
/// 
/// // Copy data into slot
/// unsafe {
///     std::ptr::copy_nonoverlapping(src, frame.data.as_mut_ptr(), len);
/// }
/// frame.actual_len = len;
/// 
/// // Use frame...
/// drop(frame); // Returns to pool
/// \`\`\`
pub fn create_frame_pool(pool_size: usize, frame_capacity: usize) -> Arc<FramePool> {
    Pool::new_with_reset(
        pool_size,
        move || FrameData::new(frame_capacity),
        FrameData::reset,
    )
}

/// Create a frame pool sized for a specific camera configuration.
/// 
/// # Arguments
/// * \`width\` - Frame width in pixels
/// * \`height\` - Frame height in pixels  
/// * \`bytes_per_pixel\` - Typically 2 for 16-bit cameras
/// * \`circular_buffer_count\` - PVCAM circular buffer size
/// 
/// Pool size is set to 2x circular buffer for consumer headroom.
pub fn create_frame_pool_for_camera(
    width: u32,
    height: u32,
    bytes_per_pixel: u32,
    circular_buffer_count: usize,
) -> Arc<FramePool> {
    let frame_bytes = (width * height * bytes_per_pixel) as usize;
    let pool_size = circular_buffer_count * 2; // 2x headroom

    tracing::info!(
        target: "pvcam_pool",
        width,
        height,
        bytes_per_pixel,
        frame_bytes,
        circular_buffer_count,
        pool_size,
        "Creating frame pool"
    );

    create_frame_pool(pool_size, frame_bytes)
}
```

