## Memory Safety Notes

### Why This is Safe

1. We acquire pool slot BEFORE copying
2. We copy from SDK buffer BEFORE unlocking
3. SDK buffer is valid until pl_exp_unlock_oldest_frame()
4. Our copy in pool slot persists independently

### Timing Diagram

```
1. get_oldest_frame() returns frame_ptr → SDK buffer locked
2. pool.acquire() → Get pool slot
3. memcpy(slot, frame_ptr) → Copy data to our slot
4. unlock_oldest_frame() → SDK buffer released (may be overwritten)
5. Send slot to consumer → Consumer owns slot
6. Consumer drops slot → Returns to pool for reuse
```

