# Sub-Epic 4: Frame Distribution Redesign

**Phase**: 3
**Parent Epic**: PVCAM Memory Pool Architecture Migration
**Depends On**: Sub-Epic 3 (Pool Integration)

## Overview

Replace the current broadcast-based frame distribution with a single-owner mpsc channel plus a tap system for secondary consumers. This enables deterministic pool reclamation.

## Current Architecture Problem

```rust
// Current: broadcast channel
pub frame_tx: tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender<Arc<Frame>>
```

Problems with broadcast for pooled frames:
1. **Multiple owners prevent pool return**: Arc<Frame> cloned to all subscribers
2. **Unpredictable lifetime**: Frame lives until last subscriber drops
3. **Pool starvation**: Slots never return if any subscriber is slow

## New Architecture: Single Owner + Taps

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      Frame Router (owns LoanedFrame)                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│         │                       │                       │                   │
│         ▼                       ▼                       ▼                   │
│  ┌─────────────┐        ┌─────────────┐        ┌─────────────┐             │
│  │Primary Sink │        │  GUI Tap    │        │  gRPC Tap   │             │
│  │(Storage)    │        │(decimated)  │        │(on-demand)  │             │
│  │             │        │             │        │             │             │
│  │OWNS frame,  │        │Gets &[u8]   │        │Gets clone   │             │
│  │drops after  │        │or Bytes     │        │as Bytes     │             │
│  │write        │        │             │        │             │             │
│  └─────────────┘        └─────────────┘        └─────────────┘             │
│         │                                                                   │
│         ▼                                                                   │
│  Pool slot returned immediately when primary drops                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Tap System Design

```rust
// New file: crates/daq-driver-pvcam/src/components/tap.rs

use crate::frame_pool::FrameData;
use parking_lot::RwLock;
use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicU64, Ordering};
use tokio::sync::mpsc;

/// Handle returned when registering a tap (for unregistration)
pub struct TapHandle {
    id: u64,
}

/// Tap types for secondary frame consumers
pub enum TapConsumer {
    /// Receives every Nth frame as Bytes (allocation on tap path only)
    /// Good for: GUI preview, network streaming
    Decimated {
        sender: mpsc::Sender<bytes::Bytes>,
        nth: usize,
    },

    /// Receives notification with shared reference (must process synchronously)
    /// Good for: Statistics, logging, lightweight monitoring
    /// WARNING: Callback blocks frame loop - keep fast!
    Reference {
        callback: Box<dyn Fn(&FrameData) + Send + Sync>,
    },

    /// Receives frame metadata only (no pixel data)
    /// Good for: Frame counters, timing analysis
    MetadataOnly {
        sender: mpsc::Sender<FrameMetadataSnapshot>,
    },
}

#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
pub struct FrameMetadataSnapshot {
    pub frame_number: u64,
    pub timestamp_ns: u64,
    pub width: u32,
    pub height: u32,
}

/// Registry for tap consumers
pub struct TapRegistry {
    taps: RwLock<Vec<(u64, TapConsumer)>>,
    next_id: AtomicU64,
    frame_counter: AtomicU64,
}

impl TapRegistry {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            taps: RwLock::new(Vec::new()),
            next_id: AtomicU64::new(1),
            frame_counter: AtomicU64::new(0),
        }
    }

    /// Register a new tap consumer
    pub fn register(&self, consumer: TapConsumer) -> TapHandle {
        let id = self.next_id.fetch_add(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
        self.taps.write().push((id, consumer));
        TapHandle { id }
    }

    /// Unregister a tap by handle
    pub fn unregister(&self, handle: TapHandle) {
        self.taps.write().retain(|(id, _)| *id != handle.id);
    }

    /// Notify all taps of a new frame
    /// Called BEFORE sending to primary consumer
    pub fn notify(&self, frame: &FrameData) {
        let count = self.frame_counter.fetch_add(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
        let taps = self.taps.read();

        for (_, tap) in taps.iter() {
            match tap {
                TapConsumer::Decimated { sender, nth } => {
                    if count % (*nth as u64) == 0 {
                        // Allocate copy for tap consumer
                        let bytes = bytes::Bytes::copy_from_slice(frame.pixels());
                        // Non-blocking send - drop if tap is slow
                        let _ = sender.try_send(bytes);
                    }
                }
                TapConsumer::Reference { callback } => {
                    // Direct callback with reference (blocks frame loop!)
                    callback(frame);
                }
                TapConsumer::MetadataOnly { sender } => {
                    let snapshot = FrameMetadataSnapshot {
                        frame_number: frame.frame_number,
                        timestamp_ns: frame.timestamp_ns,
                        width: frame.width,
                        height: frame.height,
                    };
                    let _ = sender.try_send(snapshot);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    /// Get current frame count
    pub fn frame_count(&self) -> u64 {
        self.frame_counter.load(Ordering::Relaxed)
    }
}
```

