- [ ] Only one primary consumer allowed
- [ ] Clear error if called twice
- [ ] Frame ownership transfers cleanly to consumer
- [ ] Dropping Loaned releases pool slot immediately

# Tap Decimation for GUI Preview

## Problem
GUI updates at 30-60 FPS but camera may run at 100+ FPS. Sending every frame wastes bandwidth and CPU.

## Decimation Strategies

### Option 1: Frame Skipping (Simple)
Send every Nth frame:
```rust
pub struct DecimatedTap {
    factor: u32,  // e.g., 3 = send 1/3 frames
    counter: AtomicU32,
    tx: mpsc::Sender<FramePreview>,
}

impl DecimatedTap {
    fn on_frame(&self, frame: &Loaned<FrameData>) {
        let count = self.counter.fetch_add(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
        if count % self.factor == 0 {
            // Create preview (downsampled copy)
            let preview = downsample_for_preview(frame);
            let _ = self.tx.try_send(preview);
        }
    }
}
```

### Option 2: Time-Based (Smooth)
Send at most once per interval:
```rust
pub struct TimedTap {
    interval: Duration,
    last_sent: AtomicU64,  // Instant as nanos
    tx: mpsc::Sender<FramePreview>,
}

impl TimedTap {
    fn on_frame(&self, frame: &Loaned<FrameData>) {
        let now = Instant::now().elapsed().as_nanos() as u64;
        let last = self.last_sent.load(Ordering::Relaxed);

        if now - last >= self.interval.as_nanos() as u64 {
            self.last_sent.store(now, Ordering::Relaxed);
            let preview = downsample_for_preview(frame);
            let _ = self.tx.try_send(preview);
        }
    }
}
```

### Option 3: Adaptive (Best)
Automatically adjust decimation based on consumer capacity:
```rust
pub struct AdaptiveTap {
    tx: mpsc::Sender<FramePreview>,
}

impl AdaptiveTap {
    fn on_frame(&self, frame: &Loaned<FrameData>) {
        // Only send if channel has capacity
        if self.tx.capacity() > 0 {
            let preview = downsample_for_preview(frame);
            let _ = self.tx.try_send(preview);
        }
        // If channel full, frame is naturally skipped
    }
}
```

## Recommendation: Option 3 (Adaptive)
- Self-regulating based on consumer speed
- No configuration needed
- Graceful degradation under load

