# Add Tap Methods to FrameProducer Trait

**Purpose**: Define trait methods for secondary frame consumers.

## Add to FrameProducer Trait

```rust
/// Register a tap for secondary frame access.
/// 
/// Taps receive copies (Bytes) or references, NOT ownership.
/// Multiple taps can be registered simultaneously.
/// Can be registered before or during streaming.
/// 
/// # Arguments
/// * \`tap\` - The tap consumer configuration
/// 
/// # Returns
/// * \`Ok(handle)\` - Use handle to unregister later
/// * \`Err\` if taps not supported
/// 
/// # Tap Types
/// - \`Decimated\`: Every Nth frame as Bytes (for preview/streaming)
/// - \`Reference\`: Callback with &FrameData (for stats/logging)
/// - \`MetadataOnly\`: Frame metadata without pixels
/// 
/// # Example
/// \`\`\`rust,ignore
/// // Register decimated tap for GUI preview
/// let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(10);
/// let handle = camera.register_tap(TapConsumer::Decimated {
///     sender: tx,
///     nth: 10,  // Every 10th frame
/// }).await?;
/// 
/// // Receive frames
/// while let Some(bytes) = rx.recv().await {
///     display_preview(&bytes);
/// }
/// 
/// // Cleanup
/// camera.unregister_tap(handle).await?;
/// \`\`\`
async fn register_tap(&self, tap: TapConsumer) -> Result<TapHandle> {
    anyhow::bail!("Frame taps not supported by this device")
}

/// Unregister a previously registered tap.
/// 
/// The tap will no longer receive frame notifications.
/// Safe to call even if handle is invalid (no-op).
async fn unregister_tap(&self, handle: TapHandle) -> Result<()> {
    Ok(()) // Default: no-op
}

/// Get count of active taps.
/// 
/// Useful for debugging and monitoring.
fn tap_count(&self) -> usize {
    0 // Default: no taps
}
```

