## Pool Contention Analysis

### RwLock Contention in Loaned::get()

The planmeca pool takes RwLock on every Deref. Profile this:

```rust
// Instrumented get():
pub fn get(&self) -> &T {
    let start = std::time::Instant::now();
    let slots = self.pool.slots.read();
    let lock_time = start.elapsed();

    if lock_time > Duration::from_micros(100) {
        tracing::warn!(
            target: "pool_contention",
            lock_time_us = lock_time.as_micros(),
            "Slow RwLock acquisition in pool"
        );
    }

    unsafe { &*slots[self.idx].get() }
}
```

If contention is significant, consider:
1. Caching slot reference in Loaned (unsafe but valid)
2. Using parking_lot's RwLock (already does)
