# Profile Pool RwLock Contention

**Purpose**: Verify the RwLock in Loaned::get() doesn't cause performance issues.

## The Concern

The planmeca pool takes RwLock on every Deref:

```rust
fn get(&self) -> &T {
    let slots = self.pool.slots.read();  // Lock on every access
    unsafe { &*slots[self.idx].get() }
}
```

In a hot path where frame.data is accessed multiple times, this could contend.

## Profiling Approach

### 1. Add Timing Instrumentation

```rust
// Temporary instrumentation for profiling
impl<T: Send + 'static> Loaned<T> {
    pub fn get_with_timing(&self) -> (&T, Duration) {
        let start = std::time::Instant::now();
        let slots = self.pool.slots.read();
        let lock_time = start.elapsed();

        let value = unsafe { &*slots[self.idx].get() };
        (value, lock_time)
    }
}
```

### 2. Benchmark Lock Time

```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn profile_lock_contention() {
    use hdrhistogram::Histogram;

    let pool = create_frame_pool(32, 8_000_000);
    let mut hist = Histogram::<u64>::new(3).unwrap();

