## If Contention is Found

### Option A: Cache slot reference in Loaned (Unsafe but valid)

```rust
pub struct Loaned<T: Send + 'static> {
    pool: Arc<Pool<T>>,
    idx: usize,
    // Cache the slot pointer (valid because we own the permit)
    cached_ptr: *mut T,
}

impl<T: Send + 'static> Loaned<T> {
    #[inline]
    pub fn get(&self) -> &T {
        // SAFETY: We own the semaphore permit, slot is exclusively ours
        unsafe { &*self.cached_ptr }
    }
}
```

### Option B: Remove RwLock entirely

Since the pool never shrinks, we could use a fixed array:

```rust
pub struct Pool<T> {
    slots: Box<[UnsafeCell<T>]>,  // Fixed size, no lock needed
    // ...
}
```

