Port Trigger-On-Position rapid acquisition experiment.

## Background
TOP_acquisition is CRITICAL for LIBS - it enables high-speed spectral acquisition during continuous stage motion with precise position-triggered camera frames.

## Python Original (experiments.py:373-405)
```python
def TOP_acquisition(pulses_per_shot, x_position,
                    TOP_start, TOP_end, increment, 
                    processing_laser=False):
    # Calculate offset for acceleration ramp
    offset = LIBS.xy_velocity[1]**2 / (2 * LIBS.xy_acceleration[1])
    start_position = TOP_start - offset
    end_position = TOP_end + offset

    LIBS.xy_position = (x_position, start_position)

    DA = LIBS.custom_acquire_series_TOP(
        pulses_per_shot, 'Shots', 
        'y', start_position, end_position, 
        TOP_start, TOP_end, increment
    )

    return DA, x_position
```

## Rhai Implementation
```rhai
// scripts/libs/top_acquisition.rhai
fn top_acquisition(pulses_per_shot, x_position, top_start, top_end, increment) {
    let stage = create_dover_stage();
    let cam = get_gated_camera("andor_istar");
    let spec = create_andor_spectrograph();
    let trigger = create_nidaqmx_trigger("Dev1/ctr0");

    // Calculate acceleration offset
    let velocity = stage.get_velocity();
    let acceleration = stage.get_acceleration();
    let offset = (velocity * velocity) / (2.0 * acceleration);

    let start_position = top_start - offset;
    let end_position = top_end + offset;

    // Move to start
    stage.y_move_abs(x_position);
    stage.x_move_abs(start_position);

    // Calculate number of positions
    let num_positions = ((top_end - top_start) / increment + 1.0) as i64;

    // Enable Trigger-On-Position on stage
    stage.enable_top(top_start, top_end, increment, false, 250);

    // Arm camera for multi-frame acquisition
    cam.set_num_frames(num_positions);
    cam.arm();

    // Configure trigger to match camera
    trigger.configure_pulse_train(0.1, 0.001, pulses_per_shot);

    // Start motion - stage generates triggers, camera captures
    let move_task = stage.y_move_abs_async(end_position);

    // Collect frames as they arrive
    let spectra = [];
    for i in 0..num_positions {
        let frame = cam.wait_frame();
        let position = top_start + (i as f64 * increment);
        spectra.push(#{
            y_position: position,
            spectrum: spec.apply_calibration(frame)
        });
    }

    move_task.wait();
    stage.disable_top();

    #{spectra: spectra, x_position: x_position}
}
```

## Key Coordination
1. Stage: Generates GPIO pulse at each position
2. Camera: Triggered externally by stage pulse
3. NI-DAQ: May provide additional trigger shaping if needed

## Timing Diagram
```
Stage Motion:  ----[accel]----[constant velocity]----[decel]----
Stage GPIO:         |    |    |    |    |    |    |
Camera Trig:        ↓    ↓    ↓    ↓    ↓    ↓    ↓
Frame Capture:     [F1] [F2] [F3] [F4] [F5] [F6] [F7]
```

