description:
Fix panic risk from try_lock().unwrap() in generic serial driver.

## Location
- File: crates/daq-hardware/src/drivers/generic_serial.rs
- Lines: 1424, 1430, 1441, 1458

## Current Code (BROKEN)
```rust
// Line 1424
let mut buf = self.read_buf.try_lock().unwrap();

// Line 1430
let buf = self.write_buf.try_lock().unwrap();

// Line 1441
let mut read_buf = self.read_buf.try_lock().unwrap();

// Line 1458
let mut write_buf = self.write_buf.try_lock().unwrap();
```

## Problem
`try_lock().unwrap()` will panic if the lock is already held (contention). This is especially dangerous in async code where multiple tasks may access the same driver.

## Fix Plan
Return proper errors instead of panicking:

```rust
// Option A: Return error on contention
let mut buf = self.read_buf.try_lock()
    .map_err(|_| anyhow!("Read buffer lock contention - concurrent access detected"))?;

// Option B: Use async mutex and await
