## FINAL VALIDATION COMPLETE (Gemini 2026-01-17)

### Implementation Detail 1: Shared Resource Management
**Context**: DeviceRegistry currently holds `ell14_shared_ports: RwLock<HashMap...>` for multi-drop serial.

**Problem**: daq-core must remain GENERIC - no vendor-specific fields!

**Solution**: Move shared port management to Ell14DriverFactory:
```rust
// In daq-driver-ell14/src/factory.rs
use std::sync::OnceLock;
use parking_lot::RwLock;

static SHARED_PORTS: OnceLock<RwLock<HashMap<String, Arc<Ell14Bus>>>> = OnceLock::new();

impl DriverFactory for Ell14DriverFactory {
    async fn build(&self, config: Value) -> Result<DeviceComponents> {
        let port_path = config["port"].as_str().unwrap();
        let ports = SHARED_PORTS.get_or_init(|| RwLock::new(HashMap::new()));

        // Check if port already open
        let bus = {
            let guard = ports.read();
            guard.get(port_path).cloned()
        };

        let bus = match bus {
            Some(b) => b,
            None => {
                let new_bus = Arc::new(Ell14Bus::open(port_path).await?);
                ports.write().insert(port_path.to_string(), new_bus.clone());
                new_bus
            }
        };

        // ... continue with driver creation
    }
}
```

