## CRITICAL FIX: Add Schema Support (Gemini Review 2026-01-17)

### Issue
Using serde_json::Value destroys the centralized config schema that DriverType enum provided via schemars.

### Solution: Add schema() to DriverFactory
```rust
use schemars::schema::RootSchema;

#[async_trait]
pub trait DriverFactory: Send + Sync {
    fn driver_type(&self) -> &'static str;
    fn name(&self) -> &'static str;

    /// JSON schema for this driver's configuration
    fn schema(&self) -> RootSchema;

    async fn build(&self, config: serde_json::Value) -> Result<DeviceComponents>;

    /// Validate config against schema (default impl uses schema())
    fn validate_config(&self, config: &serde_json::Value) -> Result<(), DriverError> {
        // Use jsonschema crate to validate against self.schema()
        let schema = self.schema();
        jsonschema::validate(&schema, config)?;
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

### Registry Schema Aggregation
```rust
impl DeviceRegistry {
    /// Generate complete config schema from all registered factories
    pub fn aggregate_schema(&self) -> RootSchema {
        let mut schemas = Vec::new();
        for factory in self.factories.values() {
            schemas.push(factory.schema());
        }
        // Combine into oneOf schema
        combine_schemas(schemas)
    }
}
```

### Benefits
- Config validation before driver instantiation
- Schema generation for documentation/IDE support
- Backward compatible with existing schemars usage

### Dependencies
- Add `schemars` to daq-core
- Add `jsonschema` crate for validation

