## Purpose
Migrate ELL14 rotator driver to standalone crate with self-contained shared port management.

## Location
`crates/daq-driver-thorlabs/`

## Critical: Shared Port Management
The ELL14 uses RS-485 bus - multiple devices share one serial port.
Currently `DeviceRegistry` holds the shared port map.
**Must move to module-local static.**

## Crate Structure
```
crates/daq-driver-thorlabs/
├── Cargo.toml
├── src/
│   ├── lib.rs
│   ├── ell14/
│   │   ├── mod.rs
│   │   ├── driver.rs
│   │   ├── bus.rs
│   │   ├── protocol.rs
│   │   └── shared_ports.rs  # NEW: Static port registry
│   └── future_devices/      # Placeholder for other Thorlabs
```

## shared_ports.rs (Critical Component)
```rust
use std::sync::OnceLock;
use parking_lot::RwLock;
use std::collections::HashMap;

type SharedPort = Arc<Mutex<BufReader<Box<dyn SerialPortIO>>>>;

/// Module-local registry for shared serial ports
static SHARED_PORTS: OnceLock<RwLock<HashMap<String, SharedPort>>> = OnceLock::new();

fn port_registry() -> &'static RwLock<HashMap<String, SharedPort>> {
    SHARED_PORTS.get_or_init(|| RwLock::new(HashMap::new()))
}

/// Get or create a shared port for the given path
pub async fn get_or_open_port(port_path: &str) -> anyhow::Result<SharedPort> {
    // Check if already open
    {
        let registry = port_registry().read();
        if let Some(port) = registry.get(port_path) {
            tracing::debug!(port = port_path, "Reusing existing ELL14 shared port");
            return Ok(port.clone());
        }
    }

    // Open new port
    let port_path_owned = port_path.to_string();
    let port = tokio::task::spawn_blocking(move || {
        Ell14Bus::open_port(&port_path_owned)
    }).await??;

    let shared = Arc::new(Mutex::new(BufReader::new(Box::new(port))));

    // Store in registry
    {
        let mut registry = port_registry().write();
        registry.insert(port_path.to_string(), shared.clone());
    }

    tracing::info!(port = port_path, "Opened new ELL14 shared port");
    Ok(shared)
}

/// Close all shared ports (for cleanup/testing)
pub fn close_all_ports() {
    if let Some(registry) = SHARED_PORTS.get() {
        registry.write().clear();
    }
}
```

## DriverBuilder Implementation
