notes:
## CRITICAL: Shared Port Management (Gemini Review)

### ELL14-Specific Requirement
ELL14 devices share RS-485 bus connections. Currently DeviceRegistry holds `ell14_shared_ports`.

When migrating to daq-driver-thorlabs:
1. Ell14DriverFactory MUST manage shared ports internally
2. Use static OnceLock<RwLock<HashMap>> for port map
3. Check existing connections before opening new ones
4. Multiple devices on same port share the Arc<Ell14Bus>

### Factory Implementation
```rust
use std::sync::OnceLock;
use parking_lot::RwLock;
use std::collections::HashMap;

static SHARED_PORTS: OnceLock<RwLock<HashMap<String, Arc<Ell14Bus>>>> = OnceLock::new();

pub struct Ell14Factory;

#[async_trait]
impl DriverFactory for Ell14Factory {
    fn driver_type(&self) -> &'static str { "ell14" }

    async fn build(&self, config: Value) -> Result<DeviceComponents> {
        let port = config["port"].as_str()?;
        let address = config["address"].as_str()?;

        let ports = SHARED_PORTS.get_or_init(Default::default);

        // Get or create shared bus
        let bus = {
            let guard = ports.read();
            guard.get(port).cloned()
        }.unwrap_or_else(|| {
            let bus = Arc::new(Ell14Bus::open(port).await?);
            ports.write().insert(port.into(), bus.clone());
            bus
        });

        let driver = bus.device(address).await?;
        Ok(DeviceComponents {
            device_id: config["id"].as_str()?.into(),
            movable: Some(Arc::new(driver)),
            ..Default::default()
        })
    }
}
```

This is the ONLY driver with shared resource management requirement.

