## Updated for Manual Registration (2026-01-17)

### New DeviceRegistry Design
```rust
pub struct DeviceRegistry {
    factories: HashMap<String, Box<dyn DriverFactory>>,
    devices: HashMap<String, DeviceComponents>,
}

impl DeviceRegistry {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            factories: HashMap::new(),
            devices: HashMap::new(),
        }
    }

    /// Register a driver factory (called from main.rs)
    pub fn register<F: DriverFactory + 'static>(&mut self, factory: F) {
        let driver_type = factory.driver_type().to_string();
        self.factories.insert(driver_type, Box::new(factory));
    }

    /// Initialize device from config
    pub async fn init_device(&mut self, config: Value) -> Result<String> {
        let driver_type = config["driver_type"]
            .as_str()
            .ok_or(DriverError::MissingDriverType)?;

        let factory = self.factories.get(driver_type)
            .ok_or(DriverError::UnknownDriverType(driver_type.into()))?;

        let components = factory.build(config).await?;
        let device_id = components.device_id.clone();
        self.devices.insert(device_id.clone(), components);
        Ok(device_id)
    }
}
```

### Migration Path (Strangler Fig)
1. Keep existing DriverType enum temporarily
2. Add new registry.register() path
3. Migrate one driver at a time
4. Remove DriverType variants as drivers migrate
5. Delete DriverType enum when empty

